Nigerian born midfielder, Fisayo Dele-Bashiru scored for Manchester City as they beat Shakhtar in the UEFA Youth League in the competition. Manchester City still has a chance of progressing to the knockout round of the UEFA Youth League after the win Dele-Bashiru and two other Nigeria-eligible youngsters in the shape of Gavin Bazunu and Nathanael Ogbeta were included in City’s starting line-up. Rogers opened the scoring for the Blues in the 11th minute, tapping in from close range after a shot taken by Dele-Bashiru was blocked and fell kindly for him. Although the Nigerian midfielder is claiming the assist, the official website of UEFA recorded it as an unassisted goal since a Shakhtar Donetsk player touched the ball last before Rogers struck. At minute 23, Dele-Bashiru doubled City’s advantage with a brilliant shot from 20 yards out. Writing on Instagram, the Manchester City U19s number 10 said, ”5-0 win vs Shakhtar 1 goal, 1 assist.” Fisayo Dele-Bashiru trained with the Flying Eagles in Germany before their trip to Poland for the 2019 FIFA U20 World Cup. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.